    Details:
      '<p style="text-align: justify;">Reliance Industries has reported results for fourth quarter (Q4) and year ended March 31, 2024.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">The company has reported 18.27% fall in its net profit at Rs 11,283 crore for the quarter under review as compared to Rs 13,806 crore for the same quarter in the previous year. However, total income of the company increased by 13.77% at Rs 1,54,511 crore for Q4FY24 as compared Rs 1,35,810 crore for the corresponding quarter previous year.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">On consolidated basis, the company has reported 0.39% fall in its net profit at Rs 21,243 crore for fourth quarter ended March 31, 2024 as compared to Rs 21,327 crore for the same quarter in the previous year. However, total income of the company increased by 11.91% at Rs 2,45,249 crore for Q4FY24 as compared Rs 2,19,140&nbsp; crore for the corresponding quarter previous year.&nbsp;</p><p style="text-align: justify;">For the year ended March 31, 2024, the company has reported 4.86% fall in its net profit at Rs 42,042 crore as compared to Rs 44,190 crore for the previous year. Total income of the company decreased by 0.69% at Rs 5,60,070&nbsp; crore for year under review as compared to Rs 5,63,972 crore for year ended March 31, 2023.</p><p style="text-align: justify;">For the year ended March 31, 2024, on the consolidated basis, the company has reported 6.66% rise in its net profit at Rs 79,020 crore as compared to Rs 74,088 crore for the previous year. Total income of the company increased by 3.04% at Rs 9,30,529&nbsp; crore for year under review as compared to Rs 9,03,045&nbsp; crore for year ended March 31, 2023.</p><div style="text-align: justify;"><br></div>',
